*** 

Secret Ambition (Tadhg O'Shea 4-1), barely met a rival after hitting the $750,000 Godolphin Mile front. The Satish Seemar stunner, 8, made full use of his barrier position of 2 to capture an early lead, clocking 1:35:3/10 by 6 lengths. Golden Goal and Avante Garde had no answers. Tadhg dedicated this strike to recently deceased, His Highness Sheikh Hamdan bin Rashid Al Maktoum, who sponsored Tadhg with a trip to Dubai, and he's been returning ever since. It would otherwise have been impossible. 

*** 

Subjectivist (Joe Fanning 5-1), ended a 22-year hiatus on Dubai World Cup night for Britain's winning-most trainer of all time, Mark Johnston. He smartly won the US$750,000 Dubai Gold Cup from Walderbe and Away he Goes. 

 

*** 

Brendan Walsh engaged Ryan Moore from Aiden O'Brien's stable, for Extravagant Kid, who then became the first American-trained winner of the US $1m Al Quoz Sprint beating Final Song and Acklam Express. The field had initially split into three groups, but Ryan's magic worked wonders in the final 50m. Clocking 1:09:2/10 over 1,200m, is quite something to shout about. 

*** 

Rebel's Romance (William Buick 2-1), stumped an emphatic US $750,000 UAE Derby for Charlie Appleby and Godolphin stables. Panadol was 5.5 lengths away second 

*** 

Frankie Dettori made his traditional flying dismount after the John Gosden-trained Lord North landed the US $4m Dubai Turf. First Contact flew to the front in this 1,800m race, but Lord North had plenty of energy to catch up and overtake rather spritely. Vin de Guarde and Felix followed on. 



